<aura:documentation>
	<aura:description>
		<p>
			A <code>ui:inputTextArea</code> component represents a multi-line text input control, which is rendered as an HTML <code>textarea</code> tag.
			To render the output from a <code>ui:inputTextArea</code> component, use the <code>ui:outputTextArea</code> component.
		</p>
		<p>This is a basic set up of a <code>ui:inputTextArea</code> component.</p>
		<pre>&lt;ui:inputTextArea aura:id="comments" label="Comments" value="My comments" rows="5"/></pre>
		<p>This example results in the following HTML.</p>
<pre>&lt;div class="uiInput uiInputTextArea">
    &lt;label class="uiLabel-left uiLabel">
        &lt;span>Comments&lt;/span>
    &lt;/label>
    &lt;textarea cols="20" rows="5">
    &lt;/textarea>
&lt;/div></pre>
	</aura:description>	
		<aura:example name="textarea" ref="uiExamples:textarea" label="Using ui:inputTextArea">
    	<p>This example retrieves the value of a <code>ui:inputTextArea</code> component and displays it using <code>ui:outputTextArea</code>.</p>
	</aura:example>
	
</aura:documentation>
